Argentina received a 135 million peso
($29 million) loan from CAF, the Latin American Development
Bank, to help  Rio Negro  and Neuquen provinces, which were
affected by the eruption of the Puyehue-Cordon Caulle volcano
complex in Chile.  The funds will be used to finance repair to damaged
inftraestructure in areas that were affected by the
eruption, Argentinaâ€™s Economy Ministry said in an e-mail
